getSSLSocket

public SSLSocket getSSLSocket(String host,
                              int port)
This method gets the instance of SSLSocket. It loads the KeyStore object, assign given certificate to alias. Implements the key management algorithm for KeyManagerFactory and trust management algorithm for TrustManagerFactory , gets the SSLContext object by using SSLv3 protocol and initialize the context using above management algorithm and gets the socket object.

Parameters:
host - the host name.
port - the port number.
Returns:
the SSLSocket instance.

getSSLSocket

public SSLSocket getSSLSocket(String host,
                              int port,
                              InetAddress localBindAddress)
This method gets the instance of SSLSocket. It loads the KeyStore object, assign given certificate to alias. Implements the key management algorithm for KeyManagerFactory and trust management algorithm for TrustManagerFactory , gets the SSLContext object by using SSLv3 protocol and initialize the context using above management algorithm and gets the socket object.

Parameters:
host - the host name.
port - the port number.
localBindAddress - the local address to bind the socket. May be null to indicate that the default bind should be used.
Returns:
the SSLSocket instance.

getSSLServerSocket

public ServerSocket getSSLServerSocket(int port,
                                       int backlog,
                                       InetAddress bindAddress)
                                throws Exception
This method gives the instance of SSLServerSocket object and opening port for socket communication.

Protocol used is SSLv3. Create a KeyManagerFactory instance. Initializes this factory with a source of key material. Loads a KeyStore object

Parameters:
iPort - port for opening the socket communication.
backlog - The listen backlog
iaLocal - The local InetAddress the server will bind to
Returns:
The SSLServerSocket instance
Throws:
Exception
